{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_40","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fjormundur00%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-6955-fails-java-run-io.ktor-ktor-sse-jvm-3.2.2-55b83748\n\nThe original `fails-java-run` problem looks understood and a passing candidate was preserved on that branch. The first JVM run failed because `io.ktor:ktor-sse-jvm:3.2.2` now renders SSE wire format with the `event:` line before the `data:` lines, while the generated test still expected the old order in 4 assertions (`human-intervention-logs/io.ktor:ktor-sse-jvm:3.2.2/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T08-32-48-156237Z.log`). After updating those expectations, later reruns passed both JVM and native execution (`human-intervention-logs/io.ktor:ktor-sse-jvm:3.2.2/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T08-34-04-449948Z.log`, `human-intervention-logs/io.ktor:ktor-sse-jvm:3.2.2/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T08-37-58-008581Z.log`, `human-intervention-logs/io.ktor:ktor-sse-jvm:3.2.2/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T08-38-57-430479Z.log`).\n\nThe most likely failing stage was `native-test-verify` during metadata/coverage generation, not the Java runtime fix itself. In `human-intervention-logs/io.ktor:ktor-sse-jvm:3.2.2/native-test-verify/cycle-0-generateMetadata-2026-06-06T08-35-09-750411Z.log`, `:generateMetadata` fails immediately because the JVM cannot load `native-image-agent`: `Could not find agent library native-image-agent on the library path, with error: libnative-image-agent.so: cannot open shared object file`. That also matches `stats/io.ktor/ktor-sse-jvm/3.2.2/execution-metrics.json`, which recorded `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, `metadata_entries: 0`, `code_coverage_percent: 0.0`, and no produced test/metadata artifacts.\n\nPlease inspect:\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.ktor:ktor-sse-jvm:3.2.2/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T08-32-48-156237Z.log`\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.ktor:ktor-sse-jvm:3.2.2/native-test-verify/cycle-0-generateMetadata-2026-06-06T08-35-09-750411Z.log`\n- `human-intervention-logs/io.ktor:ktor-sse-jvm:3.2.2/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T08-38-57-430479Z.log`\n\n1. Verify the environment used for `generateMetadata` so `native-image-agent` is present on the library path, then rerun metadata/coverage generation for `io.ktor:ktor-sse-jvm:3.2.2`.\n2. Reuse the preserved branch candidate, since it already updates the test expectations to the 3.2.2 SSE output ordering and passes JVM/native test reruns.\n3. Regenerate stats/coverage artifacts after fixing the agent setup, because dynamic-access coverage is currently unavailable and the metrics file is incomplete."}}
